Products.RichDescription:
Make Dinnertime Matter with Masterfoods™ Ready in 15 Minutes San Choy Bow Recipe Base 175 g


Whip up this family favourite in just 15 minutes.

Enjoy Chinese style flavours with a classic Asian blend of soy sauce, garlic & ginger.

This fast and fresh recipe base is free from artificial colours and flavours and can be enjoyed as part of your weekly diet.

Preparation: 5 Mins | Cook: 10 Mins | Serves: 4

What You'll Need:

  • Canola Oil Spray
  • 500 g lean Chicken Mince
  • 1 tin Bean Sprouts (200 g), drained
  • 1 MasterFoods™ San Choy Bow Recipe Base
  • 2 Baby Cos Lettuce, washed and separated

How To Cook:
1. Heat pan on medium heat, add oil and mince. Cook until mince is browned.
2. Add bean sprouts and Recipe Base, stir until heated through.
3. Serve your MasterFoods™ San Choy Bow in lettuce leaves.

For Something Different:
Swap the Chicken for lean beef mince

Products.RichDescription:
Make Dinnertime Matter with Masterfoods™ Ready in 15 Minutes Garlic Kebab Recipe Base
Bring a taste of the Middle East to the dinner table with Masterfoods™ Ready in 15 Minutes Garlic Kebab Recipe Base. The jaw dropping blend of garlic, parsley and mint combines to make a quick and easy Middle Eastern inspired dish the whole family will love. This fast and fresh recipe base is free from artificial colours and flavours and can be enjoyed as part of your weekly diet.

Preparation: 5 mins, Cook: 10 mins, Serves: 4

What You'll Need:
  • Canola Oil Spray
  • 500 g lean Beef Mince
  • 1 Onion (160 g), diced
  • 1 MasterFoods™ Garlic Kebab Recipe Base
  • 1/3 cup Water (80 mL)
  • 4 Flat Breads (250 g) Salad
How To Cook:
1. Heat pan on medium heat. Add oil, mince and onion cooking until browned.
2. Add Recipe Base and water to pan, stir through.
3. Allow to simmer for 3-5 minutes until heated through and sauce is reduced.
4. Serve your MasterFoods™ Garlic Kebab meal with flat breads or wraps, salad and your favourite sides.

For Something Different:
Turn it up a notch! Add a sprinkle of Masterfoods™ Chilli Flakes with Masterfoods™ Garlic Kebab Sauce.

Products.RichDescription:
Make Dinnertime Matter with Masterfoods™ Ready in 15 Minutes Smokey Taco Recipe Base 175 g


Packed full of Mexican style flavour and goodness, Masterfoods™ Ready in 15 Minutes Smokey Taco Recipe Base brings together hints of smoked paprika, onion, coriander and cumin!

This fast and fresh recipe base is free from artificial colours and preservatives and can be enjoyed as part of your weekly diet.

Preparation: 5 mins, Cook: 10 mins, Serves: 4

What You'll Need:

  • Canola Oil Spray
  • 500 g lean Beef Mince
  • 1 Onion (160 g), diced 1
  • 400 g tin Kidney Beans, drained
  • 1/3 cup Corn Kernels (80 g)
  • 1 MasterFoods™ Smokey Taco Recipe Base
  • 1/3 cup Water (80 mL)
  • 8 Tortillas (360 g)
  • Cos Lettuce

How To Cook:
1. Heat pan on medium heat. Add oil, mince and onion cooking until browned.
2. Add beans, corn, Recipe Base and water to pan, stir through.
3. Allow to simmer for 3-5 minutes until heated through. 4. Serve your MasterFoods™ Smokey Taco meal in tortillas with cos lettuce and your favourite sides.

For Something Different:
Make this a vegetarian option by swapping the lean beef mince for 500 g sliced mushrooms.


Blended with MasterFoods™ Herbs & Spices

Products.SmallFormatDescription: Masterfoods Chinese Beef Stir Fry Recipe Base
Products.FullDescription: Masterfoods Chinese Beef Stir Fry Recipe Base
Products.RichDescription:
Unlock the flavours of Asia with this soy sauce, garlic and ginger infused stir fry.

Take your tastebuds on a trip to Asia with MasterFoods™ Chinese Stir Fry Recipe Base. Made with carefully selected aromatic ingredients to add zesty notes including garlic, ginger and soy sauce. Simply add lean beef strips, red capsicum, bok choy and green beans for a delicious meal you can enjoy as part of your daily diet.

Preparation: 10 mins | Cook: 15 mins | Serves: 4

What You'll Need:
Canola Oil Spray
500 g lean Beef Strips
2 Red Capsicum (400 g), sliced
2 Bok Choy (300 g), sliced, leaves and stems separated
300 g Green Beans, trimmed and halved
1 MasterFoods™ Chinese Beef Stir Fry Recipe Base
1 cup dry Brown Rice

How To Cook:
1. Heat wok on high heat. Spray with oil and cook beef until browned.
2. Add capsicum and cook until soft.
3. Add stem of bok choy, green beans and recipe base, stir through and simmer for 3 minutes.
4. Add bok choy leaves and cook for a further 2 minutes.
5. Meanwhile cook rice to serve with your MasterFoods™ Chinese Beef Stir Fry.

For Something Different:
For a vegetarian option, swap the beef for 450 g firm tofu and 2 cubed zucchinis.

Blended with MasterFoods™ Herbs & Spices

Make Dinnertime Matter with MasterFoods™.

Products.FullDescription: Masterfoods Teriyaki Chicken Stir Fry Recipe Base
Products.RichDescription:
Add some Japanese style flavours to your midweek meals with a blend of garlic and ginger.
Put together a flavoursome family favourite in no time with MasterFoods™ Teriyaki Chicken Stir Fry Recipe Base. Made with aromatic, authentic ingredients including plenty of garlic, ginger and a hint of chilli. Simply add lean chicken breast, snow peas, carrots, red capsicum, and reduced salt soy sauce for a delicious meal you can enjoy as part of your daily diet.

Preparation: 10 mins | Cook: 15 mins | Serves: 4

What You'll Need:
Canola Oil Spray
500 g lean Chicken Breast, sliced
300 g Snow Peas, trimmed
3 Carrots (300 g), peeled & sliced
2 Red Capsicum (400 g), deseeded & sliced
2 tbsp Reduced Salt Soy Sauce (30 mL)
1 MasterFoods™ Teriyaki Chicken Stir Fry Recipe Base
1 cup dry Brown Rice

How To Cook:
1. Heat wok on medium heat, spray with oil and cook chicken until browned.
2. Add veggies and cook until soft.
3. Add soy sauce and Recipe Base, stir through and simmer for 5 minutes.
4. Meanwhile cook rice to serve with your MasterFoods™ Teriyaki Chicken Stir Fry.

For Something Different:
Make this vegetarian by swapping the chicken for 3/4 cup roasted cashews and two sliced zucchini.
Blended with MasterFoods™ Herbs & Spices

Products.RichDescription:
Create a wholesome family favourite made with a blend of ripe tomatoes, oregano and paprika.

Discover a delicious, wholesome Beef Stroganoff with that homemade taste the whole family loves, without the fuss!

A wholesome blend of tomatoes and paprika, this recipe base will keep even fussy eaters satisfied at dinnertime.

Simply add lean beef strips, onion, mushrooms and light sour cream for a delicious meal you can enjoy as part of your daily diet.

Preparation: 5 mins | Cook: 15 mins | Serves: 4.

What you'll need:
Canola Oil Spray
500 g lean Beef Strips
1 Onion (160 g), diced
200 g Button Mushrooms, sliced
1 MasterFoods™ Beef Stroganoff Recipe Base

250 g dry Pasta

How to cook:
1. Heat oil in pan and sear beef strips until brown. Set aside.

5. Meanwhile cook your favourite pasta and serve with your MasterFoods™ Beef Stroganoff.

Blended with MasterFoods™ Herbs & Spices

Products.FullDescription: Masterfoods Honey Mustard Chicken Recipe Base
Products.RichDescription:
Create a warm, tasty dinner the whole family will love.


Enjoy a wholesome, delicious homemade dinner in no time with MasterFoods™ Honey Mustard Chicken Recipe Base Sauce Pouch. Made with quality mustard seeds and honey, this Recipe Base delivers on convenience and taste. Simply add lean chicken breast, light thickened cream, green beans and carrot for a delicious meal you can enjoy as part of your daily diet.

Preparation: 10 mins | Cook: 15 mins | Serves: 4

What You'll Need:

  • Canola Oil Spray
  • 500 g lean Chicken Breast, sliced
  • 1 MasterFoods™ Honey Mustard Chicken Recipe Base
  • 1/2 cup (125 mL) Light Thickened Cream
  • 2 Carrots (200 g), peeled & thinly sliced
  • 200 g Green Beans, trimmed & halved
  • 1 cup dry brown rice

How To Cook:
1. Spray pan with oil, add chicken and cook until brown.
2. Add Recipe Base & light cream, gently stir through.
3. Add carrots and cook for 5 minutes, then add green beans & cook for another 5 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
4. Meanwhile, cook rice.
5. Give the dish a good stir and serve your MasterFoods™ Honey Mustard Chicken with warm rice.

For Something Different:
Make this a vegetarian option by swapping the chicken breast for 450 g firm tofu.


Blended with MasterFoods™ Herbs & Spices

Products.RichDescription:
Transform your sausages into a hearty and comforting meal.


Bring your family together over the dinner table for a meal together with MasterFoods™ Curried Sausages Recipe Base Sauce Pouch. A lightly flavoured tomato based sauce with a sprinkle of turmeric and cumin to deliver plenty of flavour. The perfect dinner for busy weeknights, deliver a tasty dinner in only 25 minutes. Simply add thin sausages, onion and milk for a delicious meal you can enjoy as part of your weekly diet.

Preparation: 10 mins | Cook: 10 mins | Serves: 4.

What You'll Need:

  • Canola Oil Spray
  • 8 thin Beef Sausages (600 g)
  • 1 Onion (160 g), sliced
  • 1 MasterFoods™™ Curried Sausages Recipe Base
  • 1 cup frozen Green Peas (150 g)
  • 3/4 cup Milk (188 mL)
  • 2 Carrots (200 g), peeled & sliced
  • 4 medium Potatoes (600 g), peeled, boiled & mashed

How To Cook:
1. Heat oil in pan & cook sausages until browned. Allow to cool, slice into bite-sized pieces and set aside.
2. Gently fry onion until soft, then return sausages to the pan.
3. Add Recipe Base, peas and milk, then stir through.
4. Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes or until sauce is heated through.
5. Meanwhile, steam the carrots.
6. Serve MasterFoods™ Curried Sausages with mashed potatoes and steamed carrots.

For Something Different:
Turn it up a notch! Add 1 tsp of our Chilli Flakes.


Blended with MasterFoods™ Herbs & Spices

Discover a twist on a family favourite with MasterFoods™ Tuscan Meatballs Recipe Base. A blend of balsamic vinegar, garlic and hints of rosemary. Products.RichDescription:
Teriyaki Beef

Teriyaki is a combination of two Japanese words "teri" and "yaki." Ted means a shine or lustre given by the sauce and yaki refers to the cooking method grilling or broiling. Teriyaki Beef is a savoury sweet tasting Asian dish. Lee Kum Kee's Ready Sauce is a perfect accompaniment for meats, poultry and seafood. It can also be used as a barbecue sauce. Serve with a green salad, noodles or freshly steamed rice.
